(In reply to Jan Beich from comment #9)
> (In reply to Antoine Brodin from comment #8)
> Probably. I can reproduce mplayer issue with LLD 7.0 but not 6.0[1] nor
> 5.0[2]. Being runtime issue it's not clear how many ports are affected.
> 
> [1] LDFLAGS+=-fuse-ld=lld60 + BUILD_DEPENDS+=ld.lld60:devel/llvm60
> [2] LDFLAGS+=-fuse-ld=/usr/local/llvm50/bin/ld.lld +
> BUILD_DEPENDS+=lld50:devel/llvm50

Hm, this is still strange to me.  I think we need to investigate some more if this is really not something that has changed due to another revision in lld.

E.g. https://bugs.llvm.org/show_bug.cgi?id=40176 is talking about this specific use case:

FOO {
	foo*;
};

BAR {
	*;
};

causing symbols starting with "foo" to end up in the BAR namespace with lld.  As far as I know, this has always been the case.

But with all the chromium based ports, I am not so sure.  Does anybody know what kind of linker script(s) are used in those?
